Metta, a community for entrepreneurs and innovators, has officially opened its second flagship location in Nairobi. This will be the home for entrepreneurs in East Africa.The event happened on Friday evening at the Dusit D2 Hotel in Riverside. Metta Nairobi is set to benefit local entrepreneurs, who will gain a direct access to Asia&rsquo;s thriving start-up economies.In attendance were Adlink founder Jared Babu and Eselle Group chief executive Lucile Aveva. Also present at the event were Nest Africa managing partner Aaron Fu and The Foundry CEO Roy Wachira.